 Scaling Single File Uploads (From 50MB to Multi-GBs)
The Problem: Node/Express buffers file payloads directly in memory (multer.memoryStorage()). Setting the single file limit to multiple GBs will instantly trigger Out Of Memory (OOM) crashes in standard sandboxed containers.
The Free Setup Solution:
Direct-to-Cloud Object Storage using Pre-signed URLs: Register a free account with Cloudflare R2 (comes with 10GB free storage monthly and absolutely zero egress bandwidth fees). Have your server.ts generate a temporary, secure Pre-signed upload URL, and upload the file directly from the user's browser straight to Cloudflare R2. This moves 100% of the upload load away from your server, supporting multi-gigabyte files easily.
Tus Protocol Chunking: Use chunked file uploaders to slice large documents into manageable 5MB blocks. If a network drops, the upload automatically resumes from the last successfully synced chunk.
B. Scaling Combined Data Store & Vector Storage (To Multi-GBs)
The Problem: Disk write locks and search parsing lags when a flat db.json file grows past hundreds of megabytes.
The Free Setup Solution (100% Free Managed Indexes):
Supabase (Managed PostgreSQL + pgvector): Provides a 100% Free Tier containing 500MB of database space. You can easily create a table with a VECTOR(768) column to index millions of text blocks and execute sub-millisecond cosine similarity queries natively in SQL.
Pinecone Serverless Starter Tier: Offers a shared multi-tenant index supporting up to ~100,000 vector records for free (equivalent to roughly 1GB - 2GB of raw sliced context data).
Qdrant Cloud Free Tier: Offers a managed cluster of 1GB RAM and 4GB Disk capacity for vector database search optimization, fully free.
